(d) a preliminary model to evaluate the effects of pumping on water levels and pressure.
(2) The bureau shall report the progress and results of its study to the water policy interim
committee established in 5-5-231. The committee shall consider the results of the study and make
recommendations to the legislature for department suspension or closure of new ground water appropriations
from the Fox Hills-Hell Creek aquifer.
Section 2. Codification instruction. [Section 1] is intended to be codified as an integral part of Title
85, chapter 2, part 3, and the provisions of Title 85, chapter 2, part 3, apply to [section 1].
Section 3. Effective date. [This act] is effective on passage and approval.
Section 4. Termination. [This act] terminates June 30, 2027.
